Package: bigpca
Type: Package
Title: PCA, Transpose and Multicore Functionality for 'big.matrix' Objects
Version: 1.2.0
Date: 2024-10-15
Authors@R: person(given = "Nicholas", family = "Cooper", email = "njcooper@gmx.co.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Adds wrappers that extend the 'bigmemory' ecosystem with scalable
    principal components analysis (PCA), singular value decomposition (SVD),
    matrix previewing, thinning strategies and import helpers that work with
    on-disk 'big.matrix' objects. The implementation favours numerics that are
    practical for data that do not fit in RAM.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    grDevices,
    graphics,
    stats,
    utils,
    parallel,
    methods,
    reader (>= 1.0.6),
    NCmisc (>= 1.1.6),
    bigmemory (>= 4.6.1),
    biganalytics (>= 1.1.31),
    bigmemory.sri (>= 0.1.3),
    irlba (>= 2.3.5)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.1.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: false
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
NeedsCompilation: no
SystemRequirements: A BLAS implementation such as OpenBLAS, ATLAS, or Intel MKL for
    optimal performance with the bigmemory stack.
